transcripts.text: Let's move forward and talk about tonight, what happened here.  You were here watching the folks on the stage.  Who stood out to you?

You know what I said tonight when you looked at the totality of the four hours of candidate town halls tonight?  I really thought that when Andrew Yang came out on stage at 10 o'clock at night, he brought an energy and you could feel the energy in this room.  Now, granted, we're on a college campus, but this room wasn't full of college kids.  It was full of New Hampshire Democrats with college kids here as well.  And I just thought that how he came out and his approach to answering questions.  In fact, I turned to somebody backstage when he was out there and I said, gosh, You know, when we first met Andrew Yang and we had our first town hall with him, you know, last year, it could have been around this time.  I forget.  It's all the same day now to me.  But God, he has changed.  His personality has changed.  Look at him there.  He was not like that a year ago.  His personality is now popping.
